{"findings":[{"id":"F-001","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Consensus threshold can be bypassed with duplicated signer entries","locations":["permissions/Consensus.sol:23","permissions/Consensus.sol:26","permissions/Consensus.sol:47"],"claim":"`checkSignatures` only enforces `signatures.length >= threshold` and validates each element independently; it never enforces signer uniqueness. The same authorized signer/signature can be repeated to satisfy threshold.","impact":"Multisig guarantees collapse for all `Consensus`-gated flows. Operations meant to require N distinct signers can be executed with fewer real signers, enabling unauthorized signature-queue deposits/redeems.","paths":["Configure threshold > 1 with at least one valid signer","Submit signatures array containing duplicate entries for that signer","`checkSignatures` returns true and privileged order executes"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-002","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Deposit cancellation uses oracle checkpoint value as Fenwick index","locations":["queues/DepositQueue.sol:107","queues/DepositQueue.sol:114"],"claim":"`cancelDepositRequest` reads `(exists, timestamp, index)` from `prices.latestCheckpoint()`, but for `Checkpoints.Trace224` the third return value is the checkpoint value (`priceD18`), not the request-tree index. That value is incorrectly used in `requests.modify(index, -assets)`.","impact":"Cancellations can revert (out-of-bounds Fenwick index) after reports exist, causing effective lockup of pending requests. In other states, subtraction may hit the wrong bucket and corrupt aggregate queue accounting.","paths":["User creates deposit request","Before claimability, user calls `cancelDepositRequest`","Function uses `priceD18` as Fenwick index in `requests.modify`, causing revert or wrong-bucket mutation"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-003","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Transfer whitelist check is inverted","locations":["managers/ShareManager.sol:138","managers/ShareManager.sol:139"],"claim":"With transfer whitelist enabled, `updateChecks` reverts when `from.canTransfer` is true or `to.canTransfer` is false. This inverts sender policy: non-transferable senders can pass if receiver is transferable, while transferable senders are blocked.","impact":"Transfer restriction policy is mis-enforced, allowing unauthorized transfers and blocking authorized ones.","paths":["Enable `hasTransferWhitelist`","Set sender `canTransfer=false` and recipient `canTransfer=true`","Sender transfer passes despite being non-transfer-whitelisted"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Signature queues bypass global queue pause","locations":["queues/SignatureDepositQueue.sol:11","queues/SignatureRedeemQueue.sol:13","modules/ShareModule.sol:183"],"claim":"Standard deposit/redeem queues check `isPausedQueue(address(this))`, but signature queue entrypoints do not. Pausing a queue in `ShareModule` does not stop `SignatureDepositQueue.deposit` / `SignatureRedeemQueue.redeem`.","impact":"Emergency queue pause is ineffective for signature-based flows, allowing continued state-changing operations during incidents.","paths":["Admin pauses queue with `setQueueStatus(queue, true)`","User submits signature-queue order","Order still executes because entrypoint lacks pause check"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-005","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Auto-claim on token updates can become gas-prohibitive with many queues/assets","locations":["modules/ShareModule.sol:234","modules/ShareModule.sol:238","modules/ShareModule.sol:242","managers/TokenizedShareManager.sol:46","managers/TokenizedShareManager.sol:49","managers/TokenizedShareManager.sol:52"],"claim":"`claimShares` iterates all assets and all deposit queues. `TokenizedShareManager._update` calls `claimShares` for both `from` and `to` on every transfer/mint/burn, creating O(assets*queues) overhead per token movement.","impact":"As queue/asset count grows, ordinary share transfers can exceed gas limits and fail, creating liveness failures for tokenized share operations.","paths":["Protocol accumulates many assets/queues","Any transfer triggers `_update` -> `claimShares(from)` and `claimShares(to)`","Nested iteration and external queue calls make transfers revert from gas exhaustion"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-006","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"Permissionless one-time `setVault` can be initialization-hijacked in non-atomic deployments","locations":["managers/ShareManager.sol:167","managers/RiskManager.sol:147","oracles/Oracle.sol:90","vaults/VaultConfigurator.sol:70"],"claim":"`setVault` is externally callable and only guarded by one-time initialization (`vault == 0`). If deployment/configuration is not atomic, an external caller can front-run and permanently bind a component to the wrong vault.","impact":"Initialization can be griefed or hijacked, potentially bricking intended deployment flows and forcing redeployments.","paths":["Component proxy is deployed with unset vault","Attacker calls `setVault(attackerVault)` first","Legitimate configurator call reverts with `InvalidInitialization`"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-007","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Protocol fee can be minted multiple times per period by reporting non-base assets","locations":["managers/FeeManager.sol:81","managers/FeeManager.sol:83","managers/FeeManager.sol:119","modules/ShareModule.sol:281","modules/ShareModule.sol:285"],"claim":"`calculateFee` applies protocol time-based accrual for every `handleReport` call using `timestamps[vault]`, but `updateState` only advances that timestamp when `asset == baseAsset`. Non-base asset reports therefore repeatedly charge the same elapsed interval before a base-asset report updates the checkpoint.","impact":"Repeated reporting across non-base assets can over-mint fee shares for the same time window, causing material dilution and value extraction to the fee recipient.","paths":["Timestamp checkpoint is stale for a vault","Oracle submits report(s) for non-base asset(s): each `handleReport` mints protocol fee from the same elapsed interval","Only later base-asset report updates timestamp, after over-accrual has already occurred"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-008","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Performance fee is charged on price drawdowns instead of gains","locations":["managers/FeeManager.sol:77","managers/FeeManager.sol:78","managers/FeeManager.sol:123","managers/FeeManager.sol:124"],"claim":"`calculateFee` mints performance fee when `priceD18 < minPriceD18`, and `updateState` tracks/updates a running minimum. This charges performance fees on new lows rather than on appreciation.","impact":"Users are diluted during negative performance; repeated lower prices can trigger repeated performance-fee minting, inverting expected fee economics.","paths":["Base-asset min price exists from prior reports","New lower base-asset report arrives and `calculateFee` mints performance fee","`updateState` lowers `minPriceD18`, enabling repeated fee minting on subsequent lower lows"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-009","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Disallowing a subvault asset can permanently lock already-held funds","locations":["managers/RiskManager.sol:242","managers/RiskManager.sol:243","modules/VaultModule.sol:147","modules/VaultModule.sol:148"],"claim":"`modifySubvaultBalance` reverts for any asset not in `allowedAssets[subvault]`, regardless of direction. After governance removes an asset via `disallowSubvaultAssets`, later negative balance updates needed for pulls (`_pullAssets`) also revert.","impact":"Assets already held in a subvault can become non-withdrawable after disallowing, creating permanent lockup unless special recovery exists.","paths":["Subvault holds asset X","Governance disallows X for that subvault","Any later pull path calling `modifySubvaultBalance(subvault, X, negative)` reverts with `NotAllowedAsset`"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-010","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Redeem hook can be griefed by dusting disallowed subvaults","locations":["hooks/BasicRedeemHook.sol:19","hooks/BasicRedeemHook.sol:24","hooks/BasicRedeemHook.sol:39","managers/RiskManager.sol:242","queues/RedeemQueue.sol:178","queues/RedeemQueue.sol:194"],"claim":"`BasicRedeemHook` treats raw ERC20 balances in all subvaults as liquid and tries to pull from any subvault with positive balance. If a subvault is not allowed for that asset, `hookPullAssets` reaches `modifySubvaultBalance` and reverts with `NotAllowedAsset`.","impact":"An attacker can dust tokens into a disallowed subvault and cause redemption batch handling to revert, creating permissionless DoS on affected redeem flows using this hook.","paths":["Attacker transfers dust of redeem asset A to subvault S that disallows A","Hook counts S balance as liquid and attempts pull during redeem processing","RiskManager rejects pull for disallowed asset, reverting batch handling"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-011","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Deposit accounting assumes exact ERC20 transfers and breaks on fee-on-transfer tokens","locations":["libraries/TransferLibrary.sol:46","queues/DepositQueue.sol:77","queues/DepositQueue.sol:91","queues/SignatureDepositQueue.sol:14","queues/SignatureDepositQueue.sol:18"],"claim":"ERC20 receive paths trust requested amount and do not check actual token delta after transfer. For taxed/deflationary tokens, internal accounting and minted shares are based on nominal amount while actual received amount is lower.","impact":"If such assets are supported, the protocol can mint excess shares versus real assets received, causing dilution and potential insolvency/failed redemptions.","paths":["User deposits fee-on-transfer token","Queue records/mints against full requested amount","Vault receives less than accounted, creating an accounting deficit"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-013","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"Signature redeem can burn shares from arbitrary recipients without recipient-bound authorization","locations":["queues/SignatureRedeemQueue.sol:22","queues/SignatureQueue.sol:98"],"claim":"`validateOrder` only binds `order.caller` to `msg.sender` and nonce/signatures, while `SignatureRedeemQueue.redeem` burns `order.recipient` shares. There is no on-chain requirement that the burned account authorized this redemption (e.g., recipient signature or `recipient == caller`).","impact":"If signer policy/process is compromised or misconfigured, third-party accounts can be forcibly redeemed at signer-approved terms, causing involuntary exits and economic harm.","paths":["Submit a consensus-signed redeem order with `caller=executor` and `recipient=victim`","Validation passes because caller/nonce/signatures are valid","Queue burns victim shares and transfers redemption assets to victim, forcing an unwanted unwind"],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-014","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Removing an oracle-supported asset can brick queue/risk flows and lock funds","locations":["oracles/Oracle.sol:64","oracles/Oracle.sol:153","managers/RiskManager.sol:108","queues/DepositQueue.sol:113","queues/RedeemQueue.sol:195","queues/SignatureDepositQueue.sol:20"],"claim":"`removeSupportedAssets` deletes support/report state without checking for active queues, pending requests, or existing balances. `RiskManager.convertToShares` hard-reverts via `oracle.getReport(asset)` for unsupported assets, and several core queue settlement/cancellation paths depend on it.","impact":"After removal, affected operations can revert (pending deposit cancellation, redeem batch handling, vault balance updates), creating stuck accounting and realistic fund lockup for that asset.","paths":["Privileged actor removes an asset still used by queues/positions","Subsequent flows call `RiskManager.convertToShares(asset, ...)`","`oracle.getReport(asset)` reverts `UnsupportedAsset`, bricking settlement/cancelation paths"],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"Anyone can steal all unclaimed queued shares via unrestricted `mintAllocatedShares`","source_agents":["codex_1"],"reason":"`mintAllocatedShares` calls `mint`, and `mint` enforces `onlyVaultOrQueue`; unauthorized callers revert and state changes (including `allocatedShares` decrement) roll back."},{"title":"Oracle accepts first price report as valid without validation","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"First report is marked suspicious and not propagated through `handleReport`; finalization requires privileged `ACCEPT_REPORT_ROLE`, so this is primarily trusted-role behavior, not a permissionless exploit."},{"title":"RiskManager.modifySubvaultBalance bypasses limit check for negative changes","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Limit is implemented as an upper cap on exposure; negative deltas are intentionally uncapped and external pull failure reverts the transaction, preventing silent underflow-style drain."},{"title":"RiskManager.pendingBalance tracking uses price at modify time instead of settlement","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"This is a modeling/design choice for pending exposure accounting; no concrete exploitable invariant break or direct protocol-level harm was demonstrated."},{"title":"ShareModule.claimableSharesOf iterates over all assets and queues without gas limits","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"This is a view/helper path and not a mandatory state-transition path for user funds; main liveness concern from queue iteration in token updates is already captured in F-005."},{"title":"DepositQueue.cancelDepositRequest uses wrong index from oracle checkpoint","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Duplicate of existing F-002."},{"title":"FeeManager.calculateFee has no cap on protocol fee accrual period","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Linear time-based accrual without a hard cap appears intentional fee economics rather than an implementation flaw."},{"title":"SignatureQueue validates deadline against block.timestamp without tolerance","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Strict deadline comparison is expected expiry semantics; lack of grace period is not, by itself, a security vulnerability."}]}
